#   JS-012 [structural]: test / fuzz / bench near-absent; `test.js` always `exit(0)` so CTest can't see a FAIL

`js/` has one CTest invocation and a thin `test.js`, no C++ harness / fuzz / bench,
and the test exits 0 even on failure — violating CLAUDE.md §3/§8. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  CMakeLists registers ONE test (`jabc --eval "test.run()"`); `test.js` covers only
    `test.is` + one ASCII `Encode` length; NO C++ harness, NO fuzz target, NO bench,
    NO `WITH_FUZZ`/`WITH_ASAN`/`WITH_LOAD` (violates CLAUDE.md §3/§8).
 -  `test.js` always `exit(0)` even on FAIL (`test.js:71-75`) → CTest cannot detect a
    failing test.
 -  `WITH_JS`-gated WIP; this is the meta-ticket that makes JS-002..011 verifiable.

### Goals
 -  Table-driven C++ coverage of the convert/utf8 boundary, a fuzz target, a
    round-trip bench, and a harness that exits non-zero on failure.

### Constraints
 -  Follow the project `test/`/`fuzz/`/`bench/` pattern and `WITH_*` build dirs.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  (open) Add a table-driven `test.cpp` (rows: input bytes, expect len, expect
    throw; empty / NUL / astral / invalid-UTF-8); a libFuzzer `fuzz/` target for
    convert/utf8 (corpus `$HOME/Corpus/JABC_UTF8`); a `file.write`/`read` pipe
    round-trip (catches JS-002); make the harness exit non-zero on failure.

